<br>
Having a macro PetDie that does /pet get lost will not work because you can not start the macro while casting and the pet will not go away. <br>
<br>
You can do this<br>
/cast 6   {Where 6 is the gem that has your pet}<br>
/pause XXXX  {Where XXXX is the time you want to wait}<br>
/pet get lost<br>
<br>
I have done this macro.  It works.  However, it has two major problems.   <br>
<br>
1.  If the spell fizzles, you pet is going away in XXXX and you can't stop.  Gate, or Train zone are good options at this point.<br>
<br>
<br>
2.  XXXX is highly variable.  It changes depending on the pet spell level, how busy the zone is, the type of graphics in the zone, what you are looking at.  It is best to test the macro in the enviroment you will be using it and adding a saftey factor.  <br>
<br>
I used the macro to take out Tarbul Earthstrider.  <br>
<br>
I would recommend one of the following methods over the macro method listed above.  <br>
<br>
Move your Spell gems, your window that displays casting time, and your pet control window close together.  Cast the new pet, move you mouse to the Go away button on the Pet control window.  When the spell has about one blue left to go, hit the go away button.  {Some people suggest you wait longer, but I absoultely do not want to be without a pet.  I only chain earth pets and normally the root will hold them that extra couple of seconds.}<br>
<br>
This is the method I pefer.<br>
<br>
The second method is to type /pet get lost in the text window, then cast the new pet.  Then return to the text window and hit return when you have a blue of spell left.<br>
This was the way that it had to be done before the new interface.  <br>
<br>
I have problems using this method which is why I created the above macro in the first place.  I have a highly customized the keyboard.  All of the major functions are keyed to where my lefthand normally sits on the keyboard.  My right hand sits on the numlock and controls movement.  Putting /pet get lost in the text window and then attempting to cast a spell  would more text in the text box.  It was just not convient for the way I did things.  <br>
