<br>
The other advantage is that if you screw up and pull 2 guards it is more or less impossible to win without chaining! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=anduransaryrn>Anduran Saryrn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 2:21:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8547.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chaining</span><hr size=1> If you got a nice ping you can hotkey the lot<br>
<br>
Pet cast is 10 seconds i think base (been a whlie since i chained) soooo...<br>
<br>
/cast 1  /* 1 being the number of where pet is memmed*/<br>
/pause 97 /* EQ has some timing problems with the way things are sent etc, so you pause for 97, meaning 9.7 seconds, which will give a 0.3 second buffer*/<br>
/pet get lost<br>
/pause 30 /* spell refresh time */<br>
/cast 5 /* burnout */<br>
<br>
Hope this helps some<br>
<br>
-Anduran<br>
<br>
P.S. Dont try this if you're on dialup, or change the 97 to say 95. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aj0302>AJ0302</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/03 3:06:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8547.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chaining</span><hr size=1> Nice tip Anduran!<br>
